# Cursor AI Coding Rules & Instructions

This configuration governs coding style, project conventions, and agent instructions for the US Stock & Asset Tracker codebase.

---

## 1. System Instruction for Documentation Updates (CRITICAL)

Every time code is modified, a new feature is added, or any logic is successfully fixed in each chat session, the AI Agent is strictly required to review and update the information in PROJECT_STATE.md and PROJECT_CONTEXT.md to reflect the latest status and accurate codebase state automatically before completing the task.

---

## 2. Technical Framework & Conventions

- **Tech Stack**: React (v18) + Vite + Cloudflare Pages Functions & KV.
- **Styling**: Vanilla CSS only. Do not use Tailwind CSS, styled-components, or utility classes from other frameworks unless explicitly requested by the user. Modify and scale class declarations directly in `src/index.css`.
- **No Placeholder Assets**: Avoid writing placeholder graphics or stock images. For demo views or placeholder cards, request image generation or render SVG shapes directly.
- **Maintain Comments**: Preserve existing codebase documentation, comments, and docstrings unless they conflict with the requested changes.

---

## 3. Communication Guidelines

- **File Referencing**: When mentioning files in chat responses or walkthrough summaries, always provide absolute clickable links using the `file:///` scheme (e.g. `[Dashboard.jsx](file:///d:/antigravity/us%20stock%20tracker/src/components/Dashboard.jsx)`).
- **Plan Verification**: Always create or update `implementation_plan.md` and present it to the user for feedback and approval before starting any code-modifying activities.
- **Cloud Synchronization**: Compile and build the project successfully using `npm run build` after any logic modifications, then commit and push changes immediately to the remote cloud repository.
